    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if the \"noble intention\" of these laws actually ends up hurting the people they're supposed to help, isn't it kind of a flawed policy? like, if the data shows it's more harmful than beneficial for small towns, why does it keep getting pushed so hard?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
